GAUTENG police are warning people not to open false rape cases. The warning comes after the Mamelodi family violence, child protection and sexual offences unit arrested a woman (57) on Thursday, 16 February, for perjury. According to Colonel Dimakatso Sello, the woman allegedly forced her 11-year-old niece to open a false rape case against her stepfather in 2021. REGISTER TO COMMENT! “The stepfather was then arrested and appeared before the court. However, investigation revealed that the niece was influenced by her aunt to falsely accuse him of rape,” Sello said in a statement. She added that the woman was arrested, and expected to appear in the Mamelodi Magistrates Court soon. “Community members are urged to refrain from opening false cases at police stations. Perjury is a criminal offence which is punishable by law,” said Sello.